</code></div>
</div>
<h4 id="bkmrk-create-a-github-repo">Create a GitHub repo:</h4>
<ul id="bkmrk-go-to-https%3A%2F%2Fgithub">
<li>
<p>Go to <a href="https://github.com">https://github.com</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click <strong>New Repository</strong></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Name: <code>auto-maintenance</code></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Do not check "Initialize with README"</strong></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Choose <strong>SSH</strong> URL for remote access</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="bkmrk-push-to-github%3A">Push to GitHub:</h4>
<div class="contain-inline-size rounded-2xl relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary" id="bkmrk-bash-git-init-git-ad">
<div class="flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary select-none rounded-t-2xl">bash</div>
<div class="overflow-y-auto p-4" dir="ltr"><code class="whitespace-pre! language-bash">git init
git add .
git commit -m <span class="hljs-string">"Initial commit: maintenance script"</span>
git branch -M main
git remote add origin git@github.com:yourusername/auto-maintenance.git
git push -u origin main
</code></div>
</div>
